containerized solutions configure all the privacy requirements that you need.

00:49:49.500 --> 00:49:53.659
And if you can imagine like a push button exercise where somebody presses a button and

00:49:53.659 --> 00:49:59.580
it automatically launches a container that has all the access pre-configured and associated

00:49:59.580 --> 00:50:00.379
with their profile.

00:50:01.100 --> 00:50:02.860
So that's what we call a virtual cleanroom.

00:50:02.860 --> 00:50:08.060
So it essentially means that everybody who's working off this environment is completely,

00:50:08.060 --> 00:50:12.780
you know, they're getting like a fresh, clean install, completely unperturbed by anybody

00:50:12.780 --> 00:50:14.060
else's sessions.

00:50:14.060 --> 00:50:16.379
And so it's completely independent of everybody else.

00:50:16.379 --> 00:50:18.300
And it's only being used by them.

00:50:18.300 --> 00:50:21.739
And it only has access to the data that their profile should allow them to have access to.

00:50:21.739 --> 00:50:25.100
So that's that's one way we're looking at helping clients at the moment.

00:50:25.100 --> 00:50:27.500
And one of the best practices.

00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:30.939
Yeah, I can see right now our future best practices.

00:50:30.939 --> 00:50:37.820
So it's a really exciting project.

